**Package:** `Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm`
**Service directory:** `sdk/defendereasm/Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm/`
**Triggered by:** commit 360612179 (#58563) by `@azure-sdk`

## What Changed

A new management-plane SDK for Microsoft Defender External Attack Surface Management (Defender EASM) was added. The package ships two resource types (`EasmWorkspaceResource` and `EasmLabelResource`) and a README was created with placeholder content. This is the first public release (1.0.0-beta.4).

## Gaps Found

- **Examples section is empty of real code** — only a generic link to `(aka.ms/redacted) with no EASM-specific code snippets
- **Key concepts section is generic** — only links to general Azure SDK docs; no description of what Workspaces, Labels, or Tasks are in the context of the EASM service
- **Authenticate the client has no code sample** — just links to a quickstart guide, no inline `DefaultAzureCredential` + `ArmClient` snippet
- **No `tests/Samples/` directory** — there are auto-generated samples in `tests/Generated/Samples/`, but no hand-authored snippet-backed samples that can be injected into the README via `Update-Snippets.ps1`


<strong>📐 Implementation Guide</strong>

This section contains step-by-step instructions for a coding agent to implement the changes described above.

### Step 1: Modify README.md

**File:** `sdk/defendereasm/Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm/README.md`
**Action:** Edit

Replace the current `## Key concepts`, `## Documentation`, and `## Examples` sections with the content below. The `## Documentation` section is non-standard and should be merged into the other sections.

Replace the section from `## Key concepts` through the end of `## Examples` with:

```markdown
## Key concepts

**Workspaces** are the top-level container for Defender EASM data. Each workspace is scoped to a subscription and resource group, and contains the discovered attack surface assets and associated metadata for your organization. Use `EasmWorkspaceResource` to create, read, update, and delete workspaces.

**Labels** are user-defined tags that can be applied to discovered assets within a workspace to organize and filter them. Use `EasmLabelResource` and `EasmLabelCollection` to manage labels within a workspace.

**Tasks** represent long-running operations within a workspace (for example, running a discovery run). Use `GetTaskByWorkspace` on `EasmWorkspaceResource` to poll the status of an ongoing task.

### Thread safety

All client instance methods are thread-safe and independent of each other ([more details]((azure.github.io/redacted)

### Additional concepts

[Client options](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#configuring-service-clients-using-clientoptions) |
[Accessing the response](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#accessing-http-response-details-using-responset) |
[Long-running operations](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#consuming-long-running-operations-using-operationt) |
[Handling failures](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#reporting-errors-requestfailedexception) |
[Diagnostics](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#logging) |
[Mocking]((learn.microsoft.com/redacted) |
[Client lifetime]((devblogs.microsoft.com/redacted)

## Examples

### Authenticate the client and get the workspace collection

```
TokenCredential cred = new DefaultAzureCredential();
ArmClient client = new ArmClient(cred);

string subscriptionId = &#34;&#34;;
string resourceGroupName = &#34;&#34;;
ResourceIdentifier resourceGroupResourceId = ResourceGroupResource.CreateResourceIdentifier(subscriptionId, resourceGroupName);
ResourceGroupResource resourceGroupResource = client.GetResourceGroupResource(resourceGroupResourceId);

EasmWorkspaceCollection workspaces = resourceGroupResource.GetEasmWorkspaces();
```

### Create or update a workspace

```
EasmWorkspaceData data = new EasmWorkspaceData(new AzureLocation(&#34;eastus&#34;));
ArmOperation lro = await workspaces.CreateOrUpdateAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, &#34;my-easm-workspace&#34;, data);
EasmWorkspaceResource workspace = lro.Value;
Console.WriteLine($&#34;Created workspace: {workspace.Data.Name}&#34;);
```

### List all workspaces in a resource group

```
await foreach (EasmWorkspaceResource workspace in workspaces.GetAllAsync())
{
    Console.WriteLine($&#34;Workspace: {workspace.Data.Name} in {workspace.Data.Location}&#34;);
}
```

### Create a label

```
EasmLabelCollection labels = workspace.GetEasmLabels();
EasmLabelData labelData = new EasmLabelData();
ArmOperation labelLro = await labels.CreateOrUpdateAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, &#34;my-label&#34;, labelData);
EasmLabelResource label = labelLro.Value;
Console.WriteLine($&#34;Created label: {label.Data.Name}&#34;);
```

For more code examples, see [Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm samples](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/tree/main/sdk/defendereasm/Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm/tests/Generated/Samples).
```

Also update the `### Authenticate the Client` section (under Getting started) to add a code sample:

```markdown
### Authenticate the Client

To create an authenticated client and start interacting with Microsoft Azure resources, see the [quickstart guide here](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/doc/dev/mgmt_quickstart.md).

```
